{{Quote|...Grahrk steals the princess back, escapes with her and her Mistryl guardian, blowing up an ancient temple-palace in the process, and then wants double the fee for the rescue!|[[Kubaz/Legends|Kubaz]], to the [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] guests on [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]]|<ref name="Deal" />}}
The '''Central Palace''' was an ancient structure on the [[Ocean/Legends|oceanic]] planet [[Ootoola]]. It was erected before [[4000 BBY/Legends|4000 BBY]] and had since served both as a temple and the residence of the ruling patriarch. Around [[33 BBY/Legends|33 BBY]], after the [[Revolutionary Purist Council]] seized power on the planet, the historic building was destroyed by the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Vilmarh Grahrk]] from aboard his [[Inferno (Vilmarh Grahrk)|ship]]. He hoped that the explosion would not only divert attention from the escape of [[Princess/Legends|princess]] [[Foolookoola]], but also bury the leaders of the revolutionary government under the rubble. Nevertheless, the princess's attendant, [[Naradan D'ulin]], was shocked by Grahrk's actions.<ref name="Deal" />

Over the following years, the thrilling tale of Grahrk’s daring mission and the princess’s rescue was retold in [[Cantina/Legends|cantinas]] across the Outer Rim Territories among various [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]].<ref name="R40">''[[Star Wars (1998) 40]]''</ref>

